('15','1','Guide Legal Notice','Guide Legal Notice of Guiding You','legal notice','<h1 class=\"page-heading bottom-indent\">Guiding you Guide membership terms of use</h1>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><br /><p><br /> This is the agreement that “Guiding you limited” provide for the service.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">1.Term’s definition</h2>\n<table><tbody><tr><th width=\"30%\">\n<p>Member</p>\n</th>\n<td width=\"70%\">\n<p>All of users registered the “Guiding you”</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Guest</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>Guest who made a reservation at the member of “guiding you”.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Guide</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>Company, organization and individual that register as member of “Guiding you” and registered for guide service and activity service.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Activity</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>Activity that posted when registered as guide.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Service</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>General term of activity and guide that the guide provides.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Terms</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>General terms of rules that “Guiding-you” defines.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Deal</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>Appointment that occur in “Guiding you”.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Membership information</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>general terms of the personal information that you registered your personal information when you registered as a member/host of “Guiding you”.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Guide Information</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>The information for the guide that registered as guide.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>Activity Information</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>The information of activities that registered.</p>\n</td>\n</tr><tr><th>\n<p>The site</p>\n</th>\n<td>\n<p>“The site” is the website/app of “Guiding you”.</p>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">2.Member’s Definition</h2>\n<p><br /> The member is able to use the site, based on the rules that “Guiding you limited” defined.<br /> The member is able to make an appointment of the guide, also you are able to provide the guide service/activity once registered as a guide, to experience for guest members.<br /><br /> Type of member<br /> ・Member- the member whom able to make an appointment for guide/activity.<br /> ・Guide Member- the member who is able to register the guide/activity service by themselves.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">3.Registration of Service</h2>\n<p><br /> The guide of “Guiding you” is agreed to respect the manner, law and regulation of various countries. <br /> And plans an event, translation guiding tour for the member of this site and responsible to examine each of country’s tradition.<br /> The guide only can register the service on the site that you are sure to be responsible that you do not violate the law and regulation for the rules of their country.<br /> Also providing your identification with a picture of “Guide” is required. If the particular license is required for the guiding tour or activity, the license has to have picture on it and provided to the company (Guiding you) when registered.<br /> You’re not able to register as a guide if you’re under 18 years old.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">4.The contents of registered service</h2>\n<p><br /> Although anyone can register the activity and be a guide service on this site, it is possible to be asked to delete or change the content of service you are providing if the service is inappropriate, even the service itself is legal at that country.<br /> Also it is possible the service is to be deleted without noticing, depend on the content of service.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">5.Responsibility of Guide</h2>\n<p><br /> Guide promises that the service you provide is safe and not going to put the guide in dangerous situation during the guide/activity service.<br /> Also if you are using vehicle for transportation, you are responsible to get insurance just in case.<br /> “Guiding you” have right to delete your membership and services you provide without a notice if we figured that you have not gotten the insurance. We agree that our company will not take any responsibility for the trouble occurs during the guide tour and activity.<br /> Guide promises to take responsibility to solve all the trouble and loss that happens during the activity / guide.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">6.Commission fee</h2>\n<p><br /> Once reservation is made and approved from guest, we collect 13.5% of commission fee from total amount of reservation.<br /> “3.5% is commission fee for the settlement of credit card + 10% for commission fee for this company”<br /> The balance will be paid 3business days after the date providing the service to guide’s PayPal account.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">7.Transfer to account</h2>\n<p><br /> “Guiding you”, obligate to establish the PayPal account for the guide who uses the service.<br /> The profits the guide gained through providing the service only paid at the PayPal account, and promise to not be transfer to other bank’s account.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">8.Canceling and a Penalty</h2>\n<p><br />If Gust cancel your service, canceling fee will be free before 48hours of the date of the event, 50% of canceling fee will be charged within 48hours of the date of the event.<br /> Adding to this, canceling fee is 100% on the date of the event. Canceling the service within 48 hours of the date of event, 50% of reservation fee will be paid to the account of guide, also 13.5% of settlement of credit card will be subtract. Canceling on that day, as the service is executed, the company collects 13.5% of fee.<br /> Canceling fee will be transferred within 3busineess days to PayPal accounts.<br /><br /> This is the case that penalty may occur for the Guide (host) to cancel except the reason below. <br /> The canceling that penalty fee does not occur is <br /><br /> ・when judged bad conditions of weather and disaster that might cause the accident.<br /> ・when judged the guide got bad accidents or illness that impossible to attend the service.<br /> ・when judged the service that supposed to be provided is not functioning, (For example, Restraint was closed, the equipment that uses for service is not functioning. ) However this is exception if you could have figured before that is not functioning.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">9.Member Id and Password</h2>\n<p><br /> Please check and update your password periodically to protect your member ID from others.<br /> You are responsible to manage your member ID and password by each member’s responsibility.<br /> We (Guiding you) are not responsible for illegal usages of your ID and password for your inadequate management if someone have uses for their sake.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-xs-11 col-sm-10 col-sm-push-1 cms_sentence\">\n<div class=\"cms-box\"><br /><h2 class=\"align_left\">10.Changes of registered information of the guide</h2>\n<p><br /> Along changing of your personal